Ending definitely caught me off guard; would've assumed this was a Shaggy Dog jamcon entry if I didn't know better. I think what elevates this beyond a simple bait-and-switch is how it culminates in a broken masquerade and mass casualties, but the tone and structure of the article play it off as an anticlimax. The source of the resolution probably ought to feel non-sequitur and contrived, but the imagery is so evocative of Terry Gilliam (helped by the British setting) that it just feels right somehow.







